# Praam suite — 13-layer stack

Layers are **concerns**, not deployables. Do not invent a 13th container or repo per layer.

| # | Layer | Owner | Notes |
|---|--------|--------|--------|
| 1 | Product UI | Each product repo | findoc, studio, prism, askHR, … |
| 2 | Product API | Each product repo | FastAPI / Node |
| 3 | Product domain | Each product repo | Business logic |
| 4 | Product data | Each product repo | Alembic / init in **own schema** on `praam_dev` |
| 5 | Suite identity | **praam-pulse** | JWT issuer — **not** praam-platform |
| 6 | Suite watch / events | **praam-pulse** | catalog, security_events, Raphael forward |
| 7 | Config registry | **praam-platform** | `services.yaml` |
| 8 | Config + secrets API | **praam-platform** | `platform-config` `:3180` |
| 9 | Platform SDK | **praam-platform** | `PlatformClient` — Python + TS |
| 10 | Shared Postgres | **praam-platform** | `praam_dev`, schema-per-app, pgvector |
| 11 | Shared Redis | **praam-platform** | named logical DB indexes |
| 12 | LLM gateway | **praam-platform** | LiteLLM; keys in `~/.praam/secrets.env` only |
| 13 | Dev orchestration | platform + demo-hub | `make/v1`, doctor, CI, suite `make all` |

## praam-platform scope (layers 7–12 + 13 partial)

**v1.1 is implementation-complete in this repo.** Do not add product tables, human login, or app secrets to platform.

Apps bootstrap with **only** `PRAAM_CONFIG_URL` + `PRAAM_SERVICE_TOKEN`; fetch everything else via SDK/API:

```python
from praam_platform import PlatformClient
PlatformClient("findoc-ai").load()
```

Legacy `render-env` → `.env.platform.generated` is fallback only.

## Remaining work is **outside** this repo

- Sibling apps: adopt `PlatformClient`, drop hand-edited infra env
- Wire prism, plan-copilot, pulse to platform
- Phase 2–4: Ollama, Prometheus, K8s — not v1.1 blockers

## Anti-patterns

- Moving suite auth (layer 5) into praam-platform
- Per-app DB/Redis/LLM keys in product `.env` when platform-wired
- Mutating sibling `.env` from platform scripts
- Treating 13 layers as 13 microservices locally
